The sorting of datatables cannot be understood or controlled by accessibility software such as screen readers. This makes it impossible for users with visual / motor disabilities to change the sorting on the tables.

### Describe the solution you'd like

Implement the relevant accessibility attributes, ref. https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Attributes/aria-sort

This has been introduced in Drupal 9.3, so this breaks compatibility with Drupal 8 and Drupal 9 up to version 9.2.x

I am not opposed to this, but if this gets in we have to clearly stop supporting Drupal 9.2 and below. We need to add this to `composer.json`:

```
"conflict": {
    "drupal/core": ">=8.0 <9.3"
},
```

This will ensure that any projects stuck on an old version of Drupal for any reason will not accidentally break if they update DrupalDriver. They will remain on the last supported version.

### Describe the problem

The sorting of datatables cannot be understood or controlled by accessibility software such as screen readers. This makes it impossible for users with visual / motor disabilities to change the sorting on the tables.

### Describe the solution you'd like

Implement the relevant accessibility attributes, ref. https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Attributes/aria-sort

### Describe alternatives you've considered
